'''Lindsay Dee Lohan''' ({{Pron-en|<U+02C8>lo<U+028A>.<U+0259>n}};<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.aol.com/story/_a/ap-news-pronunciation-guide-l-r/n20100418200809990003 |title=AP News Pronunciation Guide L-R |publisher=AP-News <!-- |archiveurl=http://74.125.113.132/search?q=cache:DpTP3RkCKcoJ:www.aol.com.au/news/story/AP-News-Pronunciation-Guide-L-R/578081/index.html |archivedate=March 6, 2010 -->|accessdate=March 13, 2010 }}</ref> born July 2, 1986)<ref name="cnntranscript20080727" /> is an American [[actor|actress]], [[fashion model|model]] and [[pop music|pop]] [[singer-songwriter]]. She began her career as a [[child modeling|child fashion model]] before making her motion picture debut in [[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney's]] 1998 remake of ''[[The Parent Trap (1998 film)|The Parent Trap]]'' at the age of 11.

Lohan gained further fame between 2003 and 2005 with leading roles in the films ''[[Freaky Friday (2003 film)|Freaky Friday]]'', ''[[Mean Girls]]'' and ''[[Herbie: Fully Loaded]]'', subsequently appearing in independent films including [[Robert Altman]]'s ''[[A Prairie Home Companion (film)|A Prairie Home Companion]]'' and [[Emilio Estevez]]'s ''[[Bobby (2006 film)|Bobby]]''. Her career was interrupted in 2007 as two [[Driving under the influence|DUI]] incidents and three visits to [[Drug rehabilitation|rehabilitation]] facilities led to several lost movie deals. Resuming her career, she guest starred in the TV series ''[[Ugly Betty]]'' in 2008 and filmed [[Robert Rodriguez]]'s ''[[Machete (film)|Machete]]'' in 2009.

Lohan launched a second career in pop music in 2004 with the album ''[[Speak (Lindsay Lohan album)|Speak]]'' and followed up with ''[[A Little More Personal (Raw)]]'' in 2005. She has attracted significant publicity, particularly surrounding her personal life. As such, she is often photographed by [[paparazzi]] photographers.

==Early life and education==
Lohan was born on July 2, 1986, in New York City and grew up in [[Merrick, New York|Merrick]] and [[Cold Spring Harbor, New York|Cold Spring Harbor]] on [[Long Island]], [[New York]].<ref name="cnntranscript20080727" /><ref name="nytimesmerrick20080727">{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2003/09/07/style/pulse-what-i-m-wearing-now-the-teenage-film-star.html?partner=rssnyt&emc=rss |title=Pulse: what I'm wearing Now; The Teenage Film Star |work=[[The New York Times]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |last=Tung |first=Jennifer |date=September 7, 2003 |accessdate=July 27, 2008 |quote=In real life, Ms. Lohan and her own mother, Dina Lohan, are much more compatible, especially when it comes to clothes.&nbsp;... Ms. Lohan, 17, lives in Merrick, on Long Island, when she is not filming. }}</ref> She is the eldest child of [[Dina Lohan|Donata "Dina"]] ([[married and maiden names|n<U+00E9>e]] Sullivan) and [[Michael Lohan]].<ref name="wills" /> Lindsay has three younger siblings, all of whom have been models or actors: Michael Jr. (who appeared with Lindsay in ''The Parent Trap''), [[Aliana Lohan|Aliana]] ("Ali"), and Dakota ("Cody"), the youngest Lohan child.<ref name="wills"/> Lohan is of [[Ireland|Irish]] and [[Italy|Italian]] heritage and was raised as a [[Roman Catholic Church|Catholic]].<ref name="wills" /> Her maternal family were "well known Irish Catholic stalwarts" and her great-grandfather, John L. Sullivan, was a co-founder of the [[Pro-life]] Party in Long Island.<ref name="sullivaninfo">{{cite news |last=O'Driscoll |first=Sean |coauthors=|title=The Craic; Sooooo Embarrassing! |pages= |publisher=Irish Voice |date=July 20, 2004 |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-98588526.html |accessdate=December 10, 2007 }}</ref> Lohan attended [[Cold Spring Harbor High School]], where she did well in science and mathematics<ref name="bio."/> until grade 11 when she started homeschooling.<ref name="rising">{{cite web |work=[[Interview magazine]]|publisher=Interview, Inc. |title=Lindsay Lohan: One of the movies' biggest rising stars goes on the record |author=Lynda Obst |url=http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1285/is_5_34/ai_n6041484 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20080429133107/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1285/is_5_34/ai_n6041484 |archivedate=April 29, 2008 |date=June 2004 |accessdate=August 25, 2009 |quote=Did you even get to go to high school? ... Yes. Up until the 11th grade, when I started home-schooling. }}</ref>

Lohan's parents have a turbulent history. They married in 1985, separated when she was three, and later reunited.<ref name="ap20070806">{{cite news |title=Lohan parents<U+2019> divorce heats up on Long Island |agency=Associated Press |date=August 6, 2007 |url=http://today.msnbc.msn.com/id/20152244/ |accessdate=November 12, 2008 }}</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Peretz|2006|p=}}. "Dina and Michael separated when Lindsay was just three ... But, like many young people in love, Dina took her husband back for a period."</ref> They separated again in 2005 and finalized their divorce in 2007.<ref name="sep">{{cite news |title=Lohan case illustrates flawed state system |author=Katie Thomas |date=August 10, 2007 |work=[[Newsday]] }}</ref><ref name="div">{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/6953075.stm |title=Lohan's parents end divorce row |accessdate=August 19, 2007 |date=August 18, 2007 |work=[[BBC News]]|publisher=BBC }}</ref> Her father, Michael, is a former [[Wall Street]] trader and businessman who inherited his father's pasta business and has been in trouble with the law on several occasions,<ref name="ap20070806" /><ref name="michael_02">{{cite web |work=[[Fox News]]|publisher=[[Fox Broadcasting Company]] |title=Lindsay Lohan's Dad Gets Prison Sentence |url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,157984,00.html |accessdate=July 3, 2006 }}</ref> while her mother, Dina, is a former singer and dancer.<ref name="bio."/>

==Career==
===1989<U+2013>2002: Early career and ''The Parent Trap''===
Lohan began her career as a [[child model]] with [[Ford Models]] at the age of three.<ref name="peoplebio">{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/lindsay_lohan/biography |title=Lindsay Lohan Biography: People.com |publisher=''[[People (magazine)|People]]'' <!--|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nC91TWGp |archivedate=January 31, 2010 -->|accessdate=January 31, 2010 }}</ref><ref name="rsbio">{{cite web |url=http://www.rollingstone.com/artists/lindsaylohan/biography |title=Lindsay Lohan: Biography: Rolling Stone |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |publisher=[[RealNetworks]] <!--|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nC9NQfBv |archivedate=January 31, 2010 -->|accessdate=January 31, 2010 }}</ref> She modeled for [[Calvin Klein]] Kids and [[Abercrombie Kids]], and appeared in over 100 television commercials,<ref name="bio.">{{cite web|url=http://www.thebiographychannel.co.uk/biographies/lindsay-lohan.html|title=Lindsay Lohan biography|work=[[The Biography Channel]]|publisher=[[A&E Network]]|accessdate=19 March 2010}}</ref> including those for [[Pizza Hut]] and [[Wendy's]], as well as a [[Jell-O]] spot with [[Bill Cosby]].<ref name="peoplebio" /><ref name="rsbio" /> By the age of 10, when Lohan played Alexandra "Alli" Fowler in the series ''[[Another World (TV series)|Another World]]'', ''[[Soap Opera Magazine]]'' said she was already considered a show-business veteran.<ref name="peoplebio" /><ref name="rsbio" />

Lohan remained in the role for a year, before leaving to star in [[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]]'s 1998 family comedy ''[[The Parent Trap (1998 film)|The Parent Trap]]'', a remake of the [[The Parent Trap (1961 film)|1961 movie]]. She played dual roles of estranged twin sisters who try to reunite their long-divorced parents, played by [[Dennis Quaid]] and [[Natasha Richardson]].<ref name="wills">{{cite web |publisher=[[TalkTalk]] |title=Lindsay Lohan Biography |author=Dominic Wills |url=http://www.talktalk.co.uk/entertainment/film/biography/artist/lindsay-lohan/biography/153 |accessdate=February 1, 2010 }}</ref><ref name="peoplebio" /> The film earned US[[United States dollar|$]]92&nbsp;million worldwide, and critic [[Kenneth Turan]] called Lohan "the soul of this film as much as [[Hayley Mills]] was of the original", going on to say that "she is more adept than her predecessor at creating two distinct personalities".<ref name="tptbox">{{cite web |title=The Parent Trap (1998) |url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=parenttrap98.htm |work=Box Office Mojo |publisher=[[Internet Movie Database|IMDb.com]] |accessdate=October 3, 2009 }}</ref><ref name="turan">{{cite web |work=Los Angeles Times |title=Kenneth Turan: ''The Parent Trap'' |url=http://www.calendarlive.com/movies/reviews/cl-movie980728-1,0,7316867.story |accessdate=July 29, 1998 }}</ref> The film won Lohan a [[Young Artist Award]] for best performance in a feature film<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/pastnoms20.htm |title=20th Annual Awards |publisher=The Young Artist Foundation |accessdate=October 18, 2009 }}</ref> as well as a three-film contract with Disney.<ref name="bio."/>

At the age of 14, Lohan played [[Bette Midler]]'s daughter in the pilot episode of the short-lived series, ''[[Bette (TV series)|Bette]]'', but resigned her role when the production moved from New York to [[Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles]].<ref name="wills" /><ref name="biochannel">{{cite web |url=http://www.thebiographychannel.co.uk/biographies/lindsay-lohan.html |title=Lindsay Lohan Biography |publisher=[[The Biography Channel]] |author=Sarah Barnard |accessdate=August 20, 2009 }}</ref> She also starred in two Disney [[television movie]]s: ''[[Life-Size]]'' opposite [[Tyra Banks]] in 2000, and ''[[Get a Clue]]'' in 2002.<ref name="peoplebio" /><ref name="rsbio" /> Also in 2002, Lohan dated singer [[Aaron Carter]].<ref name="peoplebio" /> There were reports of a feud between her and [[Hilary Duff]], who had also dated Carter,<ref name="peoplebio" /> though Lohan later commented that "people just started selling stories ... it was easy to write about."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elle.com/Pop-Culture/Cover-Shoots/La-Vida-Lohan |title=La Vida Lohan |date=August 13, 2006 |work=Elle | author=Isabel Dupr<U+00E9> |accessdate=February 12, 2010 }}</ref>

===2003<U+2013>2004: ''Freaky Friday'' and ''Mean Girls''===
[[File:Lindsay Lohan 2.jpg|thumb|right|Lohan in 2002|alt=A red-haired Caucasian female wearing a black coat and a hat]]
Lohan starred as Anna Coleman alongside [[Jamie Lee Curtis]] in the 2003 family comedy ''[[Freaky Friday (2003 film)|Freaky Friday]]''. At Lohan's own initiative, her character was rewritten and changed from a [[Goth subculture|Goth]] style to be more relatable.<ref>{{harvnb|Peretz|2006|p=}}. "As the script was written, the character was Goth, Lohan recalls: 'No one could relate to the character when she was really Goth. There was nothing there.' She took it upon herself to change it <U+2013> before the audition. 'I dressed really preppy,' she says. 'I wore a collared turquoise Abercrombie & Fitch shirt and khaki pants, swear to God, with a white headband. And my hair was really straight and pretty and red and blond. My agent calls and was like, "What are you doing?!{{" '}} The studio ended up re-writing the character entirely.{{' "}}</ref> Critic [[Roger Ebert]] wrote that Lohan "has that [[Jodie Foster]] sort of seriousness and intent focus beneath her teenage persona".<ref name="ebert">{{cite web |last=Ebert |first=Roger |title=Freaky Friday |url=http://rogerebert.suntimes.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20030806/REVIEWS/308060301/1023 |publisher=[[Sun-Times Media Group]] |date=August 6, 2003 |accessdate=October 3, 2009 }}</ref> ''Freaky Friday'' earned Lohan the award for [[MTV Movie Award for Best Breakthrough Performance|Breakthrough Performance]] at the [[2004 MTV Movie Awards]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/ontv/movieawards/2004/ |title=2004 Movie Awards Winners |publisher=MTV |accessdate=November 14, 2009 }}</ref> and, as of 2010, it remains her most commercially successful film, earning $160&nbsp;million worldwide<ref name="ffbox">{{cite web |title=Freaky Friday (2003) |url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=freakyfriday03.htm |work=Box Office Mojo |publisher=IMDb.com |accessdate=August 26, 2009 }}</ref> as well as an 88% approval rating on [[Rotten Tomatoes]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Lindsay Lohan <U+2013> Rotten Tomatoes Celebrity Profile |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/celebrity/lindsay_lohan/ |work=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=October 15, 2009 }}</ref>

Aiming to become a triple threat<U+2014>actor, singer and dancer, similar to [[Ann-Margret]] and [[Marilyn Monroe]]<U+2014>Lohan began showcasing her singing through her acting.<ref name="wmagazine">{{cite web |work=[[W Magazine]]|publisher=Cond<U+00E9> Nast Publications |title=Lindsay Lohan |url=http://www.wmagazine.com/celebrities/archive/lindsay_lohan?currentPage=4 |accessdate=August 5, 2008 |month=April |year=2005 |quote=it was with Ann-Margret in mind that she decided to make a foray into music. 'A lot of the people that I looked up to, the Ann-Margrets and the Marilyn Monroes, everyone was a triple threat,' she explains. 'You had to sing, dance and act, and you did it in all your movies.' }}</ref> For the [[Freaky Friday (soundtrack)|''Freaky Friday'' soundtrack]], she sang the closing theme, "Ultimate",<ref name="bio."/> as well as recording four songs for the [[Confessions of a Teenage Drama Queen (soundtrack)|''Confessions of a Teenage Drama Queen'' soundtrack]]. Producer [[Emilio Estefan, Jr.]] signed Lohan to a five-album production deal in 2002.<ref name="bio."/> Two years later, Lohan signed a recording contract with [[Casablanca Records]], headed by [[Tommy Mottola]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/lindsay-lohan/561649#/artist/lindsay-lohan/bio/561649 |title=Lindsay Lohan Biography & Awards |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=October 4, 2009 }}</ref>

In 2004, Lohan starred in two lead roles. The first, ''[[Confessions of a Teenage Drama Queen]]''<U+2014>Lohan's first role in a film that was not a remake<ref name="bio."/><U+2014>earned a domestic box office total of $29&nbsp;million, with Brandon Gray of [[Box Office Mojo]] commenting that it was "well above expectations as it was strictly for young girls".<ref name="mgbox" /> The film overall, however, did not meet with critical acclaim.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/confessions_of_a_teenage_drama_queen/ |title=Confessions of a Teenage Drama Queen (2004) |publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=October 21, 2009 }}</ref> [[Robert K. Elder]] of [[Metromix]] wrote that, "though still a promising star, Lohan will have to do a little penance before she's forgiven for ''Confessions''".<ref name="tdq_review">{{cite web |work=[[Metromix]] |title=Little to Forgive in ''Confessions'' |last=Elder |first=Robert K. |url=http://chicago.metromix.com/movies/review/little-to-forgive-in/158689/content |accessdate=October 3, 2009 }}</ref>

The teen comedy ''[[Mean Girls]]'' was Lohan's first movie independent of Disney. The film was a critical and commercial success, grossing $129&nbsp;million worldwide and, according to Brandon Gray, "cementing her status as the new teen movie queen",<ref name="mgbox">{{cite web |last=Gray |first=Brandon |title='Mean Girls' Surprisingly Nice $24.4M Weekend |url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=1325&p=.htm |work=Box Office Mojo |publisher=IMDb.com |date=May 3, 2004 |accessdate=October 3, 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/mean_girls/ |title=Mean Girls (2004) |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=Flixster, Inc. |accessdate=April 20, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Mean Girls (2004) |url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=meangirls.htm |work=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=[[Internet Movie Database]] |accessdate=October 17, 2009 }}</ref> while [[Steve Rhodes (journalist)|Steve Rhodes]] wrote that "Lohan dazzles us once more. The smartly written script is a perfect match for her intelligent brand of comedy."<ref name="rhodes">{{cite web |url=http://www.imdb.com/reviews/376/37657.html |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=Flixster, Inc. |title=Internet Reviews: Mean Girls |accessdate=January 29, 2006}}</ref> Lohan received four awards at the 2004 [[Teen Choice Award]]s for ''Freaky Friday'' and ''Mean Girls'', including Breakout Movie Star.<ref>{{cite news |work=[[The Washington Post]] |publisher|[[The Washington Post Company]] |title=NBC Sets and Spikes the Competition |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/ac2/wp-dyn/A9835-2004Aug17 |date=August 18, 2004 |accessdate=October 17, 2009 }}</ref> ''Mean Girls'' also earned her two awards at the [[2005 MTV Movie Awards]], [[MTV Movie Award for Best Performance|Best Female Performance]] and [[MTV Movie Award for Best On-Screen Duo|Best On-Screen Team]] along with several other cast members.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/ontv/movieawards/2005/ |title=2005 Movie Awards Winners |work=MTV |accessdate=November 14, 2009 }}</ref>

===2004: ''Speak''===
Lohan, then 17, became the youngest-ever host of the [[MTV Movie Awards]] in 2004.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,646426,00.html |title=''Kill Bill <U+2013> Vol. I'' tops MTV Movie Awards |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |date=June 7, 2004 |accessdate=October 18, 2009 }}</ref> Following ''Mean Girls'', which was scripted by [[Tina Fey]] and featured several alumni of ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'', Lohan hosted the show three times between 2004 and 2006, as well as hosting the 2006 [[World Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/cbbcnews/hi/newsid_6140000/newsid_6149900/6149996.stm |title=World Music Awards come to London |work=[[BBC News]] |publisher=BBC |date=November 15, 2006 |accessdate=October 3, 2009 }}</ref>

''[[Speak (Lindsay Lohan album)|Speak]]'', Lohan's debut album, was released in December 2004, peaking at number four on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]<ref name="allmusic speak">{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/cg/amg.dll?p=amg&sql=10:d9foxq8sld0e~T3|title=Speak :Lindsay Lohan|work=[[Allmusic]]|publisher=Rovi Corporation|accessdate=15 March 2010}}</ref> and earning [[RIAA certification|Platinum]] certification by early 2005.<ref name="bio."/> The album was praised by Linda McGee of [[RT<U+00C9>]], who awarded it 4 out of 5 stars and commented that "''Speak'' opens with all the raw emotion and teenage angst that you'd expect from an artist of Lohan's age" and that, "while her vocals are not sensational, their gritty edge keeps Lohan more than afloat throughout this album"<ref name="RTE"/> as well as comparing the album to the early music of [[Avril Lavigne]].<ref name="RTE">{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/arts/2005/0224/lohanl.html|title=Lindsay Lohan <U+2013> Speak|last=McGee|first=Linda|year=2004|publisher=[[Raidi<U+00F3> Teilif<U+00ED>s <U+00C9>ireann]]|accessdate=19 March 2010}}</ref> [[Allmusic]], however, awarded it 2 out of 5 stars and claimed the album "feels more like a byproduct of an overdriven, overamplified celebrity culture than an actual album".<ref name="speak review">{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/cg/amg.dll?p=amg&sql=10:d9foxq8sld0e|title=''Speak'' Review|last=Erlewine|first=Stephen Thomas|year=2004|work=[[Allmusic]]|publisher=[[Rovi Corporation]]|accessdate=19 March 2010}}</ref> Though primarily a [[pop music|pop]] album, ''Speak'' was introduced with the single "[[Rumors (song)|Rumors]]". Described by ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' as "a bass-heavy, angry club anthem",<ref name="rumors">{{cite web |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |publisher=[[RealNetworks]] |title=Lindsay Lohan: Rumors |url=http://www.rollingstone.com/artists/lindsaylohan/albums/album/6490352/rid/6507507 |accessdate=January 27, 2006 }}{{dead link|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/artists/lindsaylohan/albums/album/6490352/rid/6507507|date=May 2010}}</ref> "Rumors" details Lohan's complaints with the paparazzi<ref name="MTV Rumors">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1490964/20040914/lohan_lindsay.jhtml|title=For The Record: Quick News On Lindsay Lohan|date=September 14, 2004|work=[[MTV]]|publisher=[[Viacom]]|accessdate=19 March 2010}}</ref> and eventually earned a [[Gold record|Gold]] certification in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?resultpage=1&table=SEARCH_RESULTS&action=&title=Rumors&artist=Lindsay%20Lohan&format=SINGLE&debutLP=&category=&sex=&releaseDate=&requestNo=&type=&level=&label=&company=&certificationDate=&awardDescription=&catalogNo=&aSex=&rec_id=&charField=&gold=&platinum=&multiPlat=&level2=&certDate=&album=&id=&after=on&before=on&startMonth=1&endMonth=12&startYear=2005&endYear=2005&sort=Artist&perPage=10|title=Rumors|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]]|accessdate=19 March 2010}}</ref>

While shooting ''[[Herbie: Fully Loaded]]'' in 2004, Lohan was hospitalized with a kidney infection brought on by stress in her personal life and of recording her first album while the film was in production, prompting ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]'' to label it Lohan's "first disastrous shoot".<ref name="Peretz 2006 p"/> The magazine also described how Lohan terminated the promotional tour and was de-emphasized on the movie poster due to "un-Disney-like behavior".<ref name="Peretz 2006 p">{{harvnb|Peretz|2006|p=}}.</ref> Guest starring in an episode of ''[[That '70s Show]]'', where he was a regular, Lohan dated actor [[Wilmer Valderrama]] in 2004.<ref name="peoplevalderrama">{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,781868,00.html|title=Lindsay Lohan, Wilmer Valderrama Split |work=[[people (magazine)|People]] |publisher=Time Inc. }}</ref> According to ''Vanity Fair'', the breakup with Valderrama contributed to Lohan's issues during the shooting of ''Herbie: Fully Loaded''.<ref name="Peretz 2006 p"/>

With ''Mean Girls'', Lohan's public profile was raised significantly and [[paparazzi]] began following her.<ref>{{cite news |last=Binelli |first=Mark |title=Confessions of a Teenage Drama Queen |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |publisher=[[RealNetworks]] |date=August 19, 2004 |url=http://www.rollingstone.com/news/coverstory/lindsay_lohan_teenage_drama_queen/page |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20080308202138/http://www.rollingstone.com/news/coverstory/lindsay_lohan_teenage_drama_queen |archivedate=2008-03-08 |quote=All of which resulted in Lohan becoming a favorite object of scrutiny for the paparazzi and the online pervert community alike. |accessdate=August 20, 2008 }}</ref> She spent several years living out of hotels in Los Angeles, of which two years were spent at [[Chateau Marmont Hotel|Chateau Marmont]]. In late 2007, after settling down in more permanent residence, she explained that she spent so much time in hotels because she "didn't want to be alone" but that "it wasn't a way of life ... not very consistent."<ref>{{harvnb|Peretz|2006|p=}}. "After Mean Girls, Lohan moved into the Four Seasons in Los Angeles <U+2013> alone."</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Apodaca|2008|p=}}. "After years of living like a rock star in hotels <U+2014> a year at the Hollywood Roosevelt, followed by two years and two suites at the Chateau Marmont <U+2014> Lindsay wanted to go home. Which meant actually creating a home. Last fall, she took the keys to a Beverly Hills estate she leases with Semel. It took her five years of living in Los Angeles, where she moved when she was a squeaky-sweet 16, to finally settle down."</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Kaylin|2008|p=}}. "Whereas Lohan used to live in hotels <U+2013> 'I didn't want to be alone, so whatever I needed I could just go downstairs and there were people there' <U+2013> she now recongizes the unhealthiness of that. 'It wasn't a way of life,' she says. 'Not very consistent.{{' "}}</ref> Lohan has had a series of [[car accident]]s that have been widely reported, with minor crashes in August 2004,<ref name="rearend">{{cite web |work=[[Fox News]]|publisher=[[Fox Broadcasting Company]] |title=Lindsay Lohan Sued Over Car Accident |url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,146228,00.html |accessdate=March 4, 2007 }}</ref> October 2005,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1510909/20051004/lohan_lindsay.jhtml |title=Lindsay Lohan Taken To Hospital After Car Accident |author=Corey Moss |co-author=Gil Kaufman |date=October 5, 2005 |publisher=MTV.com |accessdate=December 7, 2007 }}</ref> and November 2006, when Lohan suffered minor injuries because a [[paparazzi|paparazzo]] who was following her for a photograph hit her car. Police called the crash intentional, but prosecutors said there was not enough evidence to file criminal charges.<ref name="paparazzo_01">{{cite web |work=[[Newsday]] |title=Photog Gets Break after Lohan Crash |url=http://www.newsday.com/entertainment/news/ny-flashtwo4569547dec30,0,6838959.story |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20060114105430/http://www.newsday.com/entertainment/news/ny-flashtwo4569547dec30,0,6838959.story |archivedate=January 14, 2006 |accessdate=October 2, 2009 }}</ref>

===2005: ''Herbie: Fully Loaded'' and ''A Little More Personal (Raw)''===

[[Image:Herbie.jpg|thumb|Herbie, the car that appears with Lohan in ''[[Herbie: Fully Loaded]]'' (2005)|alt=A white [[Volkswagen Beetle]] with a racing stripe across the middle and the number 53 on the front and the door]]
Lohan returned to Disney in 2005 for ''[[Herbie: Fully Loaded]],'' the fifth film in the series with the [[anthropomorphism|anthropomorphic]] car [[Herbie]]. ''Fully Loaded'' earned $144&nbsp;million worldwide and received mixed reviews.<ref>{{cite web |title=Herbie: Fully Loaded (2005) |url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=herbie05.htm |work=Box Office Mojo |publisher=IMDb.com |accessdate=January 25, 2006 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/herbie_fully_loaded/ |title=Herbie: Fully Loaded (2005) |publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=October 17, 2009 }}</ref> [[Stephen Holden]] of ''[[The New York Times]]'' called Lohan "a genuine star who ... seems completely at home on the screen",<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2005/06/22/movies/22herb.html |title=Lord Love a VW Bug That Knows Its Mind |date=June 22, 2005 |author=[[Stephen Holden]] |work=[[The New York Times]]|publisher=The New York Times Company |accessdate=October 17, 2009 }}</ref> While [[James Berardinelli]] wrote that, "as bright a starlet as she may be, Lohan ends up playing second fiddle to the car."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.reelviews.net/php_review_template.php?identifier=1188 |title=Herbie: Fully Loaded |author=[[James Berardinelli]] |publisher=ReelViews |accessdate=October 17, 2009 }}</ref>

In 2005, Lohan became the first person to have a [[My Scene]] [[celebrity doll]] released by [[Mattel]]. She also voiced herself in the animated direct-to-DVD film ''[[My Scene Goes Hollywood]]'', based on the series of dolls.<ref name="doll">{{cite web |author=Larry Carroll |publisher=vh1.com |title=Lohan Still A Redhead On Toy-Store Shelves, In Cartoons |url=http://www.vh1.com/movies/news/articles/1507565/08122005/story.jhtml |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20071001020110/http://www.vh1.com/movies/news/articles/1507565/08122005/story.jhtml |archivedate=2007-10-01 |accessdate=December 3, 2006 }}</ref>

Lohan's second album, ''[[A Little More Personal (Raw)]]'', was released in December 2005, debuting at number 20 on the Billboard 200 chart, falling under the top 100 within six weeks.<ref name="bio."/> ''[[Slant Magazine]]'' called it "contrived&nbsp;... but for all the so-called weighty subject matter, there's not much meat on these bones."<ref name="slant">{{cite web |work=[[Slant Magazine]] |title=Slant magazine: Music Review: A Little More Personal (Raw)|url=http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/lindsay-lohan-a-little-more-personal-raw/686 |accessdate=January 29, 2006 }}</ref> The album was certified Gold in early 2006.<ref name="itunes raw">{{cite web |url=http://itunes.apple.com/us/artist/lindsay-lohan/id20541815|title=Lindsay Lohan|work=[[Itunes store]]|publisher=[[Apple Inc.]]|accessdate=14 March 2010}}</ref> The music video for the album's first single, "[[Confessions of a Broken Heart (Daughter to Father)]]", was directed by Lohan and featured the acting debut of her sister, Ali.<ref name="bio."/> The video was a dramatization of the pain Lohan says her family has suffered at the hands of her father.<ref name="coabh_video">{{cite web |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |title=Lohan Puts "Heart" into Second Album |url=http://www.billboard.com/news/lohan-puts-heart-into-second-album-1001219529.story#/news/lohan-puts-heart-into-second-album-1001219529.story |accessdate=April 20, 2010 }}</ref> It was Lohan's first song to chart on the ''[[Billboard Hot 100]]'', peaking at number 57.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/retrieve_chart_history.do?model.vnuArtistId=561649&model.vnuAlbumId=7503500 |title=Artist Chart History <U+2013> Lindsay Lohan |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20070311151809/http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/retrieve_chart_history.do?model.vnuArtistId=561649&model.vnuAlbumId=750350 |archivedate=March 11, 2009 |accessdate=October 4, 2009 }}</ref>

Lohan's parents legally separated in December 2005 and finalized their divorce in 2007.<ref name="sep"/><ref name="div"/> Lohan spoke in 2007 about her childhood: "I feel like a second parent in the sense that I helped raise my family." ... "I was put between my mother and father a lot. Well, I would put myself between them to try and keep the peace, and I felt good doing that."<ref name="Bachrach 2007 p">{{harvnb|Bachrach|2007|p=}}.</ref> Despite the conflicts, Lohan calls herself "a family girl" and has spoken very fondly of her family, including her father.<ref>{{harvnb|Apodaca|2008|p=}}. {{" '}}I'm a family girl. I love my family. I love them to death. They're amazing, and that's something you can't take for granted.{{' "}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Binelli |first=Mark |title=Confessions of a Teenage Drama Queen |publisher=Rolling Stone |date=August 19, 2004 |quote=... the best dad. He's the most loving, kind person you could ever meet.}}</ref> However, in 2007 and again in 2008 she stated that she was no longer in contact with him, describing his unpredictable behavior as hard to deal with.<ref>{{harvnb|Bachrach|2007|p=}}. "...&nbsp;gossip items starring her father. 'I don't speak to him,' she tells me."</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Kaylin|2008|p=}}. "she's shutting down communication with Dad for a bit <U+2013> 'until he decides to be a grown-up.' Family turmoil's been a constant for a while now. 'It was always up and down,' Lohan says of her teen years <U+2013> 'very unpredictable. It was just of just like whether he was gonna be there, what he would be like; we didn't know what to expect from him, which was difficult.{{' "}}</ref><ref name="harpers2008-12">{{cite web |last=Heyman |first=Marshall |title=Lindsay Lohan: Myth vs. Reality |work=Harper's Bazaar |date=December 2008 |url=http://www.harpersbazaar.com/magazine/cover/lindsay-lohan-cover-story-1208 |quote=The two are not speaking at the moment, though Lindsay insists, "He's not a bad guy. He's just making bad choices." |accessdate=December 15, 2008 }}</ref> In November 2009, her father released recordings of private phone calls with and about Lohan to the media.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20318141,00.html |title=Lindsay Lohan's Dad Says God Is Punishing Her |date=November 6, 2009 |first=Tim |last=Nudd |work=[[People Magazine]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |accessdate=December 15, 2009 }}</ref> She commented on [[Twitter]]: "I haven't had a real relationship w/Michael Sr. in years."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20317833,00.html |title=Lindsay Lohan Stands Up to Her Father |date=November 5, 2009 |first=Mike |last=Fleeman |work=[[People Magazine]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |accessdate=December 15, 2009 }}</ref>

Lohan's next widely released film, the romantic comedy ''[[Just My Luck (2006 film)|Just My Luck]]'', opened in May 2006 and, according to ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', earned Lohan over $7&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117915397.html |title=Thesp Lohan bids adieu to Endeavor |date=December 22, 2004 |first=Cathy |last=Dunkley |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |publisher=[[Reed Business Information]] |accessdate=October 21, 2009 }}</ref> The opening weekend box office takings of $5.7&nbsp;million "broke lead actress Lindsay Lohan's winning streak" according to Brandon Gray.<ref>{{cite web |last=Gray |first=Brandon |title='Poseidon' Capsizes, Cruise Clings to Top Spot |url=http://boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=2067&p=.htm |work=Box Office Mojo |publisher=IMDb.com |date=May 15, 2006 |accessdate=October 21, 2009 }}</ref> The film received poor reviews and earned Lohan her first [[Golden Raspberry Awards|Golden Raspberry]] nomination for [[Razzie Award for Worst Actress|worst actress]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Just My Luck (2006) |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=Flixster, Inc. |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/just_my_luck/ |accessdate=April 16, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://razzies.com/history/06nomActr.asp |title=Razzies<U+00A9> 2006 Nominees for Worst Actress |accessdate=October 18, 2009 }}</ref>

===2006<U+2013>2007: Independent movies and career interruptions===
Following ''Just My Luck'', Lohan focused on smaller roles in more mature, [[independent film|independent movies]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Goldman |first=Andrew |title=La Vida Lohan |work=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]] |publisher=[[Hachette Filipacchi M<U+00E9>dias]] |date=September 2006 |url=http://www.elle.com/Pop-Culture/Cover-Shoots/La-Vida-Lohan |accessdate=August 20, 2008 |quote=her recent choices to take small roles in more adult-themed independent films}}</ref> [[Robert Altman]]'s ensemble comedy ''[[A Prairie Home Companion (film)|A Prairie Home Companion]]'', in which Lohan co-stars with [[Meryl Streep]] and [[Lily Tomlin]], had a [[limited release]] in June 2006. [[Peter Travers]] wrote for ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' that "Lohan rises to the occasion, delivering a rock-the-house version of [[Frankie and Johnny (song)|'Frankie and Johnny']]".<ref name="aphcreview">{{cite web |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |title=Rolling Stone:'' A Prairie Home Companion'': Review |url=http://www.rollingstone.com/reviews/movie/_/id/9200812/rid/10466862/ |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20060612234127/http://www.rollingstone.com/reviews/movie/_/id/9200812/rid/10466862/ |archivedate=2006-06-12 |accessdate=June 14, 2006 }}</ref> Co-star Streep said of Lohan's acting: "She's in command of the art form" and "completely, visibly living in front of the camera".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wmagazine.com/celebrities/archive/lindsay_lohan_meryl_streep |title=Two Queens |date=May 2006 |first=Kevin |last=West |work=[[W magazine]] |publisher=[[Cond<U+00E9> Nast Publications]] |accessdate=December 15, 2009 }}</ref> The [[Emilio Estevez]] drama ''[[Bobby (2006 film)|Bobby]]'' was released in theaters in November 2006. Lohan received favorable comments for her performance, particularly a scene opposite [[Sharon Stone]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Hornaday |first=Ann |title='Bobby' Turns Back the Clock To a Fateful Day |work=[[The Washington Post]] |publisher=[[The Washington Post Company]] |date=November 23, 2006 |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/11/22/AR2006112202099.html |quote=... that generation is most effectively embodied by a character named Diane (Lindsay Lohan), who is planning to marry a boy she knows only vaguely to keep him from going to Vietnam. When she explains what she's doing to a manicurist played by Sharon Stone, the unspoken wisdom between the two women is palpable and quietly electrifying. |accessdate=November 4, 2008 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Macdonald |first=Moira |title=Poignant story gets a lift from heavyweight cast |work=[[The Seattle Times]] |publisher=[[The Seattle Times Company]] |date=December 21, 2006 |url=http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/movies/2003443730_bobby23.html |quote=But for every moment that sags, another soars. Lindsay Lohan is tremulous and sweet as Diane. ... Sharon Stone<nowiki>['s]</nowiki> ... scenes with Lohan ... are surprisingly gentle. |accessdate=November 4, 2008 }}</ref> As part of the ''Bobby'' ensemble cast, Lohan was nominated for a [[Screen Actors Guild Awards|Screen Actors Guild Award]] and won an award for Ensemble Acting at the [[Hollywood Film Festival]] where she also won a Breakout Award for her work in 2006.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2007/01/17/entertainment/main2369558.shtml |title=Lindsay Lohan Enters Rehab |work=[[CBS News]] |publisher=[[CBS]] |date=January 17, 2007 |author=Judy Faber |quote=She's up for a SAG award as part of the ensemble cast of "Bobby." |accessdate=November 14, 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://hollywoodawards.com/news/2006/honorees_nominees.html |title=Hollywood Film Festival<U+00AE> News |publisher=Hollywood Network, Inc |accessdate=November 14, 2009 }}</ref> Lohan's next appearance was in ''[[Chapter 27]]'' as a [[John Lennon]] fan who befriends [[Mark David Chapman]] ([[Jared Leto]]) on the day he murders Lennon. Filming finished in early 2006, but was not released until March 2008 due to difficulties in finding a distributor.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lindsay finally getting to grow up onscreen |url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/1032771181.html?dids=1032771181:1032771181&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=May+06%2C+2006&author=John+Hiscock&pub=Toronto+Star&desc=Lindsay+finally+getting+to+grow+up+onscreen&pqatl=google|first=John |last=Hiscock |work=[[Toronto Star]] |publisher=[[Torstar]] |date=May 6, 2006 |quote=has just finished Chapter 27 }}</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Halbfinger|2007|p=}}. "Another finished film starring Ms. Lohan and Jared Leto, 'Chapter 27,' ... won critical support at the Sundance Film Festival but has not found a distributor."</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=chapter27.htm |title=Chapter 27 (2008) |work=Box Office Mojo |publisher=IMDb |accessdate=October 3, 2009 |quote=Widest Release: 11 theaters, Release Date: March 28, 2008 }}</ref> In May 2007, the drama ''[[Georgia Rule]]'', in which Lohan stars alongside [[Felicity Huffman]] and [[Jane Fonda]], was released. [[Owen Gleiberman]] of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' wrote that "Lohan hits a true note of spiteful princess [[narcissism]]".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20038337,00.html |title=Georgia Rule (2007) |author=[[Owen Gleiberman]] |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|date=May 9, 2007 |accessdate=October 18, 2009 }}</ref> During filming in 2006, Lohan was hospitalized, her representative saying "she was overheated and dehydrated".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,26334,1219436,00.html |title=Lindsay Lohan Sent to the Hospital |date=July 26, 2006 |work=[[People Magazine]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |accessdate=December 15, 2009 }}</ref> At the time Lohan was going through a breakup with restaurant owner [[Harry Morton]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,26334,1538390,00.html|title=Lindsay Lohan & Harry Morton: It's Over? |work=[[People Magazine]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |date=September 22, 2006 |accessdate=April 17, 2010}}</ref> This contributed to her problems on the set according to ''[[Allure (magazine)|Allure]]''.<ref name="Bachrach 2007 p"/> In a letter that was made public, studio executive [[James G. Robinson]] called Lohan "irresponsible and unprofessional". He mentioned "various late arrivals and absences from the set" and that "we are well aware that your ongoing all night heavy partying is the real reason for your so-called 'exhaustion'."<ref name="ap-spoiledchild">{{cite web |url=http://today.msnbc.msn.com/id/14087536/ |publisher=Associated Press via [[msnbc.com]] |title=Studio exec: Lohan 'acted like a spoiled child' |date=July 29, 2006 |accessdate=October 2, 2009 }}</ref> Co-star Fonda later commented that "when she showed up on the set, she was always great."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elle.com/Pop-Culture/Cover-Shoots/Girl-On-Fire/Lindsay-Lohan |title=Girl On Fire |date=August 2, 2007 |first=Holly |last=Millea |work=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]] |publisher=[[Hachette Filipacchi M<U+00E9>dias]] |accessdate=December 15, 2009 }}</ref>

In 2006, Lohan attended [[Alcoholics Anonymous]] meetings.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/story/0,668,20860420-5006009,00.html|title=Lohan faces alcohol demons |date=December 3, 2006 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph (Australia)]] |publisher=[[News Limited]] |accessdate=April 17, 2010}}</ref> In early January 2007, production on the film ''[[I Know Who Killed Me]]'' was put on hold when Lohan underwent [[Appendicectomy|appendix surgery]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20006632,00.html |title=Appendix Surgery for Lindsay Lohan |date=January 5, 2007 |work=[[People Magazine]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |accessdate=April 17, 2010 |quote=Lindsay Lohan had surgery to remove her appendix on Thursday. "She does have appendicitis, and she is getting her appendix removed," her rep, Leslie Sloane, told PEOPLE Thursday afternoon. }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20008812,00.html |title=Lindsay Lohan Checks Into Rehab |date=January 18, 2007 |work=[[People Magazine]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |accessdate=April 17, 2010 |quote=Lohan, 20, has been filming the thriller I Know Who Killed Me, and a rep for the movie tells PEOPLE production had already been on hold due to Lohan's recent appendix surgery. It's uncertain when filming will resume. }}</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Finn|2007|p=}}. "Production had already been halted at the beginning of January, when Lohan took a timeout for an appendectomy. She received the go-ahead from her doctor to go back to work early last week."</ref> Later in the month, Lohan admitted herself to the Wonderland Center [[Drug rehabilitation|rehabilitation]] facility. Lohan checked out on February 16, 2007 after completing a 30-day stay.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://usmagazine.com/linsday_lohan_0|title=Us Exclusive: Lohan Enters Rehab|work=[[Us Weekly]] |publisher= [[Wenner Media]] |date=January 18, 2007 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20071111105050/http://usmagazine.com/linsday_lohan_0|archivedate=November 11, 2007 |accessdate=April 6, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nowmagazine.co.uk/celebrity-news/234745/lindsay-lohan-leaves-rehab/1/ |title=Star checks out of treatment centre |work=[[NOW (British magazine)|NOW]] |publisher=[[IPC Media]] |date=February 19, 2007 |accessdate=April 6, 2010}}</ref> During the stay she continued shooting the film, returning to the facility at night.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20008812,00.html |title=Lindsay Lohan Checks Into Rehab |date=January 18, 2007 |work=People |quote=Lindsay Lohan has checked into rehab, she said in a statement Wednesday. 'I have made a proactive decision to take care of my personal health,' she said. "I appreciate your well wishes and ask that you please respect my privacy at this time.' }}</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Finn|2007|p=}}. "Per her rep, Lohan has been free to work and carry on with her life during the day and head back to Wonderland at night. She returned to the set of the upcoming thriller I Know Who Killed Me Jan. 26, nine days after starting treatment. 'She's on set today,' Zelnik added."</ref> Shortly thereafter, Lohan withdrew from a film adaptation of [[Oscar Wilde]]'s ''[[A Woman of No Importance]]'', her publicist stating that Lohan needed to "focus on getting better".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20010614,00.html |title=Lindsay Lohan Backs Out of Upcoming Movie |accessdate=January 12, 2009 |last=Dagostino |first=Mark |date=February 1, 2007 |work=[[People Magazine]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |quote=Lindsay Lohan, who entered rehab last month, has backed out of an upcoming movie, A Woman of No Importance, her rep confirms to PEOPLE. ... Rather than jumping from movie to movie, Lohan plans to take it easy for a few weeks, according to Sloane, who adds: 'It's a mature thing to do. ... She's doing this so she can focus on getting better.' }}</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Finn|2007|p=}}. "Planning to take it easy for a while once she completes rehab for what ails her, Lindsay Lohan has opted to drop out of one of her upcoming film projects, the big-screen adaptation of the Oscar Wilde play A Woman of No Importance. 'She's doing great,' Lohan's publicist, Leslie Sloane Zelnik, told E! Online senior editor Marc Malkin, adding that she needs to focus on her treatment for now."</ref> Lohan was replaced in ''[[The Edge of Love]]'' in April 2007, shortly before filming was to begin, with the director citing "insurance reasons" and Lohan later explaining that she "was going through a really bad time then."<ref>{{cite news |title=In brief: Miller replaces Lohan as Dylan Thomas' wife |date=April 24, 2007 |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/2007/apr/24/dylanthomas |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |accessdate=January 12, 2009 | location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Love, cinema, Dylan and stardom |date=June 1, 2008 |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/wales/mid_/7429831.stm |work=[[BBC News]] |publisher=BBC |accessdate=January 12, 2009 |quote=Maybury said he had originally wanted Parent Trap actress Lindsay Lohan to play Thomas's wife, but he was unable to get her out of California to Wales for "insurance reasons".}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Lindsay Lohan |date=February 2009 |url=http://www.interviewmagazine.com/film/lindsay-lohan/2/ |work=[[Interview Magazine]] |publisher=Brant Publications |accessdate=January 12, 2009 |quote=I spoke to John Maybury [director of ''Edge of Love''] when I was in London ... I was supposed to do a movie for him three years ago, but I was going through a really bad time then. }}</ref>

Lohan was then cast in the film adaptation of the novel ''[[Poor Things]]''. On May 26, four days before production was set to start, she was arrested for [[Driving under the influence|DUI]] and subsequently re-entered rehab. The film's producers initially voiced support and production was put on hold.<ref>{{cite news |first=Dave |last=McNary |title=Lindsay Lohan enters rehab |date=May 29, 2007 |url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117965946.html?categoryid=13&cs=1 |work=Variety |accessdate=January 12, 2009|quote=The thesp was arrested for suspicion of driving under the influence Saturday after her convertible struck a curb, and investigators found what they believe is cocaine at the scene, police said. She admitted herself to an intensive medical rehabilitation facility, according to a statement released by her publicist, Leslie Sloane Zelnick. ... Zelnick told Daily Variety on Tuesday that she did not know if Lohan will be able to take part in "Poor Things," a dark comedy set to begin shooting on Wednesday. A rep for the producers said the project's still moving ahead and may have to switch schedules. }}</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Halbfinger|2007|p=}}. "Production of 'Poor Things' ... was initially to have begun May 30, but was derailed four days earlier when Ms. Lohan crashed her Mercedes and was charged with driving under the influence ... and she checked herself into the Promises rehabilitation facility. ... 'Poor Things' was put on hold."</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Hollywood Execs Don't Like Lindsay Fully Loaded |date=May 31, 2007 |url=http://www.usmagazine.com/lindsay_lohan_13 |work=Us Magazine |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20070602120610/http://usmagazine.com/lindsay_lohan_13 |archivedate=June 2, 2007 |accessdate=January 12, 2009 |quote=Producers Rob Hickman and Shirley MacLaine, who had recently signed Lohan to star in their film, ''Poor Things'', released the following statement about Lindsay's involvement: 'In the spirit of helping Lindsay Lohan and her rehabilitation, we have been asked by Lindsay to comply with her wishes to continue working on ''Poor Things.'' We are trying to rearrange the shooting schedule to facilitate her working at the end of the shoot, to coincide with the completion of her rehabilitation. We wish her love and the blending of mind, body and spirit.' }}</ref>

Lohan was involved in a traffic accident on May 26, 2007 when she lost control of her car and ran the vehicle up a curb. Beverly Hills police also found what they preliminarily identified as a "usable" amount of [[cocaine]] in her car. After receiving treatment for minor injuries, Lohan was arrested on a misdemeanor charge of [[driving under the influence]] of alcohol.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2007/WORLD/europe/05/26/saturday/index.html |title=Police: Actress Lindsay Lohan arrested for driving under the influence of alcohol |publisher=CNN |date=May 26, 2007 |accessdate=April 18, 2010 }}</ref> She subsequently entered the [[Promises Treatment Center]] rehabilitation facility, where she stayed for 45 days.<ref name="AP/CBS">{{cite news |title=Lindsay Lohan Returns To Rehab |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2007/05/29/entertainment/main2865462.shtml |publisher=Associated Press via [[CBS News]] |first= |last= |date=May 29, 2007 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/article/index.jsp?uuid=0cfded22-b4ef-4393-a654-33c78665e6b7 |title=Lindsay Leaves Rehab Behind |author=Natalie Finn |date=July 15, 2007 |publisher=[[E!]] |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20070929135915/http://www.eonline.com/news/article/index.jsp?uuid=0cfded22-b4ef-4393-a654-33c78665e6b7 |archivedate=September 29, 2007 |accessdate=October 2, 2009 }}</ref> Upon her release to outpatient care, Lohan was voluntarily fitted with a [[ankle monitor|SCRAM bracelet]] to monitor her sobriety.<ref name="knbcjuly24">{{cite news |url=http://www.knbc.com/entertainment/13742793/detail.html |title=Lindsay Lohan Arrested For DUI, Narcotics Possession |publisher=[[KNBC]] |date=July 24, 2007 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20070927015213/http://www.knbc.com/entertainment/13742793/detail.html |archivedate=September 27, 2007 |accessdate=October 1, 2009 }}</ref><ref name="timesjuly24">{{cite web |url=http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/entertainment/2003804583_lohan25.html |title=Just out of rehab, Lohan arrested again on DUI, drug charges |work=[[The Seattle Times]] |publisher=[[The Seattle Times Company]] |date=July 25, 2007 |accessdate=April 18, 2010 }}</ref>

On July 24, three weeks before filming was scheduled to resume, Lohan was arrested for a second DUI and again returned to rehabilitation.<ref>{{harvnb|Halbfinger|2007|p=}}. "the larger casualty of Ms. Lohan<U+2019>s latest encounter with the law ... is 'Poor Things' ... filming was to have started in three weeks."</ref> Ultimately she fell out of the project.<ref>{{cite news |first=Carly |last=Mayberry |title=Murphy latest 'Hall' monitor |date=February 6, 2008 |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/film/news/e3i67f661e87c3de3d3cf48ad446951d906 |work=Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=August 22, 2009 |quote=Lohan fell out of the ["Poor Things"] project in May when she admitted herself to a rehabilitation facility.}}</ref>

On July 24, less than two weeks after leaving Promises, Lohan refused a field sobriety test in [[Santa Monica]] and was taken to a police station where her blood alcohol level was found to be above the legal limit. While conducting a search, the police found a small amount of cocaine in her pocket.<ref name="knbcjuly24" /><ref name="timesjuly24" /><ref name="apjuly24">{{cite web |url=http://news.aol.com/entertainment/movies/story/_a/arrested-lohan-says-i-am-innocent/20070725064409990001 |title=Arrested Lohan Says 'I Am Innocent' |publisher=Associated Press via AOL News |date=July 25, 2007 |accessdate=October 3, 2009 }}</ref> Lohan was booked on a felony charge of possession of cocaine and misdemeanor charges of driving under the influence and driving with a suspended license.<ref name="apjuly24" /><ref>{{cite news |url=http://film.guardian.co.uk/apnews/story/0,,-6804025,00.html |title=Lindsay Lohan: 'I Am Innocent' |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] <!-- |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20071122042048/http://film.guardian.co.uk/apnews/story/0,,-6804025,00.html |archivedate=November 22, 2007 -->|accessdate=October 3, 2009 | location=London}}</ref> In August 2007, Lohan entered Cirque Lodge Treatment Center in [[Sundance, Utah|Sundance]], [[Utah]] for a third stint at rehabilitation, staying until discharge on October 5, 2007.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20058562,00.html|title=Lindsay Lohan Leaves Rehab |work=[[People Magazine]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |date=September 25, 2007 |accessdate=April 18, 2010}}</ref> In 2007 Lohan first dated British TV personality [[Calum Best]] and then snowboarder Riley Giles, who she met during her third stay in rehab.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20038781,00.html|title=Lindsay Lohan & Calum Best's Romantic Escape |date=May 14, 2007 |work=[[People Magazine]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |accessdate=April 18, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20169048,00.html |title=Dina Lohan: Riley 'Took Desperate Measures to Hurt Lindsay' |work=[[People Magazine]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |date=January 3, 2008 |accessdate=April 18, 2010 }}</ref>

In the wake of her second DUI arrest, Lohan withdrew from a scheduled appearance on ''[[The Tonight Show with Jay Leno]]'' in which she had been due to promote ''I Know Who Killed Me'', a [[Low-budget film|low-budget]] thriller-mystery in which she stars as a [[stripper]] with a dual personality.<ref>{{harvnb|Halbfinger|2007|p=}}.</ref> The film premiered to what ''Entertainment Weekly'' called "an abysmal $3.5&nbsp;million".<ref name="ew">{{cite web |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20049806,00.html |title=I Know Who Killed Your Career |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |date=August 7, 2007 |accessdate=April 18, 2010 }}</ref> It earned Lohan a dual [[Golden Raspberry Awards|Razzy]] nomination for [[Razzie Award for Worst Actress|Worst Actress]], with Lohan coming first and second, tying with herself.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.razzies.com/history/07winners.asp |title=28th Annual Golden Raspberry (Razzie) Award <U+201C>Winners<U+201D> |work=razzies.com |accessdate=April 20, 2010 }}</ref>

Hollywood executives and industry insiders commented that it would be difficult for Lohan to find employment until she could prove that she was sober and reliable, citing possible issues with securing insurance.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2007/05/31/movies/31loha.html |title=For Lohan, a Mix of Sympathy and Scorn |work=[[The New York Times]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |first=Sharon |last=Waxman |date=May 31, 2007 |quote=...would not hire her until she proved herself healthy and reliable" ... "She would need perhaps to post her salary as bond, or pay for her own insurance, even on an independent film. |accessdate=August 17, 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/story?id=3409556 |title=From Rising Star to 'Unemployable' Actress |publisher=[[ABC News]] |first=Sheila |last=Markar |date=July 24, 2007 |quote=...unemployable until she proves she can stay clean, sober and free of charges." ... "Securing insurance, a necessary and costly step for making any movie, could be all but impossible if Lohan is involved in the project. |accessdate=August 17, 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117969119.html?categoryid=22&cs=1 |title=Lindsay Lohan claims innocence |date=July 25, 2007 |publisher=Associated Press via ''Variety'' |accessdate=November 15, 2009 |quote=All Hollywood productions need insurance, and troublesome or troubled actors can often stand in the way of that requirement. ... 'I don't see how she's employable for the next 18 months' ... 'Who's going to insure her?' }}</ref> [[James G. Robinson|Robinson]], the producer who previously criticized Lohan's work ethic on ''Georgia Rule'', said that he would work with her again if she got the proper medical care, and went on to describe her as "one of the most talented young women in the movie business today."<ref name="ew"/>

On August 23, 2007, Lohan pleaded guilty to cocaine use and driving under the influence and was sentenced to one day imprisonment and 10 days [[community service]]. She was also ordered to pay fines and complete an alcohol education program, and was given three years [[probation]]. Lohan released a statement in which she said "it is clear to me that my life has become completely unmanageable because I am addicted to alcohol and drugs".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://today.msnbc.msn.com/id/20412029/|title=Lindsay Lohan Reaches Plea Deal, Will Serve One Day In Jail; 'I Relapsed,' Actress Says|accessdate=August 25, 2007 |date=August 23, 2007 |publisher=[[MSNBC]] }}</ref> On November 15, 2007, Lohan served 84 minutes in jail. A sheriff spokesman cited overcrowding and the nonviolent nature of the crime as reasons for the reduced sentence.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://today.msnbc.msn.com/id/21824406/|title=Lindsay Lohan spends 84 minutes in jail |publisher=Associated Press via [[MSNBC]] |date=November 15, 2007 |accessdate=April 18, 2010}}</ref> The probation was extended by an additional year in October 2009, following several instances in which Lohan failed to attend the court-ordered substance abuse treatment classes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://today.msnbc.msn.com/id/33334694/ns/entertainment-celebrities/ |publisher=Associated Press via [[MSNBC]] |title=Judge adds another year to Lohan<U+2019>s probation |date=October 16, 2009 |accessdate=October 18, 2009 }}</ref>

Following a switch to [[Universal Motown]], Lohan began working on a third album, tentatively titled ''Spirit in the Dark'', in late 2007 and released "[[Bossy (Lindsay Lohan song)|Bossy]]" in May 2008.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.allmusic.com/cg/amg.dll?p=amg&sql=11:0ifexqtaldae~T1 |title=Lindsay Lohan Biography |publisher=allmusic |accessdate=April 18, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20166542,00.html |title=Lindsay Lohan: 'It Was Time to Grow Up' |date=December 14, 2007 |work=[[People Magazine]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |accessdate=April 18, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rollingstone.com/rockdaily/index.php/2008/06/26/lindsay-lohan-plots-third-album/ |title=Lindsay Lohan Nabs Hitmakers for Third Album |date=June 26, 2008 |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |accessdate=January 8, 2010 }}{{dead link|date=May 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/news/lindsay-lohan-gets-bossy-on-new-track-1003805736.story |title=Lindsay Lohan Gets 'Bossy' On New Track |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=May 7, 2008 |accessdate=April 18, 2010 }}</ref> In November 2008, Lohan stated that work on the album had stalled and that she wanted to avoid the stress of working on movies and music at the same time.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/lindsay-lohan-says-she-avoided-finishing-her-new-album_article_12166 |title=Lindsay Lohan Says She Avoided Finishing Her New Album |date=November 13, 2008 |work=[[Access Hollywood]] }}</ref>

===2008 onwards: Continued career===
In May 2008, Lohan made her first screen appearance since ''I Know Who Killed Me'', on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]'s television series ''[[Ugly Betty]]''.<ref name=beeb>{{cite news |title=Lohan gets Ugly Betty guest role |date=May 6, 2008 |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/7385054.stm |work=[[BBC News]] |publisher=BBC |accessdate=January 12, 2009 }}</ref> She guest starred in four episodes, spanning seasons two and three in 2008, as [[Kimmie Keegan]], an old schoolmate of the protagonist [[Betty Suarez]].<ref name=beeb/>
Lohan made a cameo appearance in the drug themed music video for the May 2008 [[N*E*R*D]] song "[[Everyone Nose]]".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1584718/20080403/nerd.jhtml|title=MTV News <U+2013> N.E.R.D. Video Shoot <U+2013> Featuring Lindsay Lohan <U+2013> Erupts Into Brawl |publisher=MTV |date=April 3, 2008 |accessdate=April 18, 2010}}</ref>

Lohan has been the face of [[Jill Stuart (fashion designer)|Jill Stuart]], [[Miu Miu]], and [[Dooney and Bourke]], as well as the 2008 [[Visa Inc.|Visa]] Swap British fashion campaign<ref name="nydailynews.com">{{cite web |last=Boyko |first=Olga |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/lifestyle/fashion/2009/01/10/2009-01-10_lindsay_lohan_peddles_fornarina.html |title=Lindsay Lohan peddles Fornarina |publisher=[[Daily News (New York)|Daily News]] |date=January 10, 2009 |accessdate=October 4, 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.visaswap.com/face.html |title=Visa Swap |publisher=[[Visa Inc.|Visa Europe]] |year=2008 |accessdate=October 3, 2009 }}</ref> as well as being the face of Italian clothing company Fornarina for its Spring/Summer 2009 campaign.<ref name="nydailynews.com" />

Lohan dated DJ [[Samantha Ronson]] in 2008 and 2009.<ref name="harperdec2008">{{cite web |url=http://www.harpersbazaar.com/magazine/cover/lindsay-lohan-cover-story-1208-2|title=Lindsay Lohan: Myth vs. Reality |work=[[Harper's Bazaar]] |publisher=[[Hearst Communications, Inc.]] |accessdate=April 18, 2010 |first=Marshall |last=Heyman }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://omg.yahoo.com/news/lindsay-lohan-in-tears-i-m-in-absolute-hell/20973?nc |title=Lindsay Lohan in Tears: I'm in 'Absolute Hell' |work=[[Us Magazine]] ''via'' [[Omg!]] |date=April 8, 2009 |accessdate=October 3, 2009 }}</ref> Lohan co-hosted club events with Ronson and accompanied her when she was DJ-ing.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/story?id=5475432 |title=Who Is Samantha Ronson? |date=July 30, 2008 |first=Sheila |last=Marikar |publisher=[[ABC News]] |accessdate=February 12, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://today.msnbc.msn.com/id/28509103/ns/entertainment-access_hollywood/ |title=Lohan, Ronson may have split after public spats |date=January 5, 2009 |work=[[Access Hollywood]] via [[MSNBC]] |accessdate=February 12, 2010 |quote=Lohan and Ronson, who were hosting a bash together at club Mansion }}</ref> Speaking about her sexual orientation, Lohan has said she is not a [[lesbian]]. When asked if she is [[bisexual]], she responded "Maybe. Yeah", adding "I don't want to classify myself."<ref name="harperdec2008" /> In April 2009, following her break up with Ronson, Lohan appeared in a skit on the comedy website [[Funny or Die]]. The [[Self-deprecation|self-deprecating]] video is a spoof of the personal ads on dating website [[eHarmony]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theinsider.com/news/2018466_Lindsay_Lohan_makes_mock_dating_service_ad |title=Lindsay Lohan makes mock dating service ad |work=[[Associated Press]] ''via'' [[The Insider (newspaper)|The Insider]] |date=April 14, 2009 |accessdate=October 2, 2009 }}</ref> It was viewed 2.7 million times in the first week and received favorable comments from the media.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/celebritynews/5186659/Lindsay-Lohans-spoof-personal-ad-is-viewed-by-2.7m.html |title=Lindsay Lohan's spoof personal ad is viewed by 2.7m |date=April 20, 2009 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |accessdate=April 18, 2010 |quote=Robin Roberts, the anchorman for ABC news, said of the two minute mock personal: 'It's not just getting laughs, it may get her career back on track.' | location=London}}<!-- NB: link not dead as shown on Checklinks tool --></ref>

In the 2009 comedy ''[[Labor Pains]]'', Lohan plays a woman who pretends to be pregnant. During the shoot, Lohan's manager worked with the paparazzi to encourage the media to show her working, as opposed to partying.<ref>{{harvnb|Kaylin|2008|p=}}. "But Muro <nowiki>[Lohan's manager]</nowiki> is also strategic <U+2013> for instance, welcoming paparazzi shots of Lohan on the set, working (as opposed to tumbling out of a club). As such, whenever Lohan is called to the set, she dutifully does the pap walk <U+2013> texting feverishly behind a curtain of hair, while grungy lensmen scamper alongside."</ref> It was originally planned for a theatrical release, but instead appeared as a TV movie on the [[ABC Family]] cable channel in July 2009, "a setback for the star" according to ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]''.<ref name=uswkly>{{cite web |url=http://omg.yahoo.com/news/lindsay-lohans-new-movie-goes-straight-to-cable/20472 |title=Lindsay Lohan's New Movie Goes Straight to Cable |work=[[omg!]] |publisher=[[Yahoo!]] |date=March 26, 2009 |accessdate=April 19, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.variety.com/review/VE1117940693.html?categoryid=32&cs=1 |title=Labor Pains |date=July 16, 2009 |work=Variety |accessdate=October 31, 2009 }}</ref> The premiere received 2.1&nbsp;million viewers, "better-than-average" for the channel according to [[E! Online]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://uk.eonline.com/uberblog/b135139_did_lindsay_lohan_movie_bomb.html |title=So, Did That Lindsay Lohan Movie Bomb? |date=July 21, 2009 |publisher=E! Online |accessdate=October 31, 2009 }}</ref> Joanna Weiss of ''[[The Boston Globe]]'' commented that Lohan "looks to be coasting through a part that requires little effort, anyway".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.boston.com/ae/tv/articles/2009/07/17/pregnancy_plot_barely_holds_water_in_labor_pains/ |title=Pregnancy plot barely holds water |date=July 17, 2009 |work=[[The Boston Globe]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |first=Joanna |last=Weiss |accessdate=October 31, 2009 }}</ref> [[Alessandra Stanley]] of the ''[[New York Times]]'' said "this is not a triumphant return of a prodigal child star. ... [''Labor Pains''] never shakes free of the heavy baggage Ms. Lohan brings to the role".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/17/arts/television/17labor.html?_r=1 |title=What to Expect When You<U+2019>re Lying |date=July 16, 2009 |work=[[The New York Times]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |first=Alessandra |last=Stanley |accessdate=October 31, 2009 }}</ref>

Lohan was a guest judge on US TV style contest ''[[Project Runway]]'' sixth season premiere episode, which aired in August 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://omg.yahoo.com/news/access-exclusive-lindsay-lohan-guest-judges-project-runway-season-six-premiere/13278 |title=Lindsay Lohan Guest Judges 'Project Runway' Season Six Premiere |work=[[Access Hollywood]] ''via'' [[Omg!]] |date= September 19, 2008 |accessdate=October 3, 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/showtracker/2009/08/project-runway-back-with-a-vengeance.html |title='Project Runway': Back with a vengeance! |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |publisher=[[Tribune Company]] |date=August 21, 2009 |accessdate=April 19, 2010 }}</ref> In December 2009, she spent a week in [[India]] working on a [[BBC Three]] documentary on [[Human trafficking|trafficking]] of women and children.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/celebritynews/6772147/BBC-helps-Lindsay-Lohan-save-children-in-India.html |title=BBC helps Lindsay Lohan save children in India |date=December 9, 2009 |first=Tim |last=Walker |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |accessdate=December 15, 2009 | location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20326926,00.html |title=Lindsay Lohan Returns From India |date=December 13, 2009 |first=David |last=Caplan |work=[[People Magazine]] |publisher=[[time Inc.]] |accessdate=December 15, 2009 }}</ref> She is due to appear in [[Robert Rodriguez]]'s ''[[Machete (film)|Machete]]'', for which she was filming in August and September 2009 and which is scheduled for release on September 3, 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/lindsay-lohan-heads-back-to-work-shoot-is-going-great_article_21640 |title=Lindsay Lohan Heads Back To Work: <U+2018>Shoot Is Going Great!<U+2019> |work=[[Access Hollywood]] |date=August 13, 2009 |accessdate=August 15, 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20305137,00.html |title=Lindsay Lohan Is Not in a Psych Ward |date=September 17, 2009 |work=[[People Magazine]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |quote=Lohan's rep tells PEOPLE the actress is indeed working, and is currently in Texas shooting the upcoming thriller Machete |accessdate=October
 3, 2009 }}</ref>

In April 2010, Lohan was cast as actress [[Linda Lovelace]], star of [[Deep Throat (film)|''Deep Throat'']] in an upcoming film entitled ''Inferno''. It will be directed by Matthew Wilder and produced by Chris Hanley.<ref name="lovelace">{{cite news|url=http://www.okmagazine.com/2010/04/lindsay-lohan-to-portray-xxx-star-linda-lovelace-in-inferno/|title=Lindsay Lohan to Portray XXX Star Linda Lovelace in <U+2018>Inferno<U+2019>|last=Oppenheim|first=Gena|date=April 17, 2010|work=[[OK!]]|publisher=[[Northern & Shell]]|accessdate=April 30, 2010}}</ref> On May 19, 2010, it was announced she was cast in another film called ''Black Friday'', which is a 3D horror film.<ref>http://www.movieweb.com/news/NE9ZYeacQPZddc</ref>

==Other work and personal life==
During the [[2008 US presidential campaign]], Lohan offered her services to [[Barack Obama]]'s election effort, including hosting events aimed at young voters; but her offer was declined. An unnamed source within the Obama campaign told the ''[[Chicago Sun-Times]]'' that Lohan was "not exactly the kind of high-profile star who would be a positive for us."<ref>{{cite news |first=Bob |last=Zwecker |title=Barack Obama campaign nixes Lindsay Lohan |date=September 17, 2008 |url=http://www.webcitation.org/5c3ezxUsu |work=[[Chicago Sun Times]] |accessdate=November 3, 2008 }}</ref> She nonetheless posted [[MySpace]] blogs with her opinions on the election, urging voters to support Obama, criticizing media coverage of vice-presidential candidate [[Sarah Palin]], and describing Palin as [[homophobic]], [[anti-abortion]] and [[anti-environmentalism|anti-environmentalist]].<ref name="eonline.com">Pederson, Erik. [http://www.eonline.com/uberblog/b28941_lindsay_lohan_smacks_sarah_palin_with.html "Lindsay Lohan Smacks Sarah Palin With Post"]. [[E! Online]], September 14, 2008. Retrieved July 31, 2009.</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.marieclaire.co.uk/news/celebrity/273974/lindsay-lohan-s-attack-on-sarah-palin.html |title=Lindsay Lohan's Attack on Sarah Palin |publisher=[[Marie Claire|marieclaire.co.uk]] |date=September 17, 2008 |accessdate=July 31, 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Lohan gets political on blog, sounds off on Palin |publisher=Associated Press via [[The Insider (TV series)|The Insider]] |date=September 2, 2008 |url=http://www.theinsider.com/news/1160539_Lohan_gets_political_on_blog_sounds_off_on_Palin |accessdate=October 2, 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Lindsay Lohan Blasts Palin on Blog |publisher=[[Fox News Channel|FOXNews]] |date=September 15, 2008 |url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,422585,00.html |accessdate=September 26, 2008 }}</ref> Lohan had earlier in 2006, during the [[Iraq War]], expressed an interest in going to Iraq on a [[United Service Organizations|USO]] tour with [[Hillary Rodham Clinton|Hillary Clinton]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Goldman |first=Andrew |title=La Vida Lohan |work=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]] |date=September 2006 |url=http://www.elle.com/Pop-Culture/Cover-Shoots/La-Vida-Lohan |quote=I've been trying to go to Iraq with Hillary Clinton for so long. Hillary was trying to work it out, but it seemed too dangerous. I wanted to do what Marilyn Monroe did, when she went and just set up a stage and did a concert for the troops all by herself. |accessdate=August 20, 2008 }}</ref> Back in 2004, Lohan stated that she did not like to talk about politics in order to avoid alienating any part of her fanbase.<ref>{{cite web |last=Binelli |first=Mark |title=Confessions of a Teenage Drama Queen |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=August 19, 2004 |url=http://www.rollingstone.com/news/coverstory/lindsay_lohan_teenage_drama_queen/page |quote=On reaching voting age: 'I'm not very politically involved. And I don't like to talk about it. I mean, if you say you're a Democrat, that'll turn off Republicans, and that's half of your fan base.' |accessdate=September 26, 2008 }}</ref>

Lohan has featured in various [[men's magazine]]s. She was voted tenth on the list of "100 Sexiest Women" by readers of ''[[FHM]]'' in 2005,<ref name="FHM">{{cite news |work=[[USA Today]] |publisher=[[Gannett Company]] |title=Jolie sizzles atop ''FHM'' sexiest list |url=http://www.usatoday.com/life/people/2005-03-23-fhm-sexiest-women_x.htm?POE=LIFISVA |date=March 23, 2005 |accessdate=September 29, 2006 | first1=C<U+00E9>sar G. | last1=Soriano}}</ref> while ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]'' placed her third on its" Hot 100" list in 2006<ref name="Maxim">{{cite web |work=[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]] |title=2006 Hot 100 |url=http://www.maxim.com/girls/hot-100/77965/2006-hot-100.html?src=GM7070:MD |accessdate=March 18, 2007 }}</ref> and first in 2007.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.maximonline.com/Girls/Lindsaylohan/slideshow/1125/47.aspx?src=GM7070:MD |title=2007 Hot 100 <U+2014> 1. Lindsay Lohan |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20071206005632/http://www.maximonline.com/Girls/Lindsaylohan/slideshow/1125/47.aspx?src=GM7070:MD |work=[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]] |archivedate=December 6, 2007 |accessdate=October 2, 2009 }}</ref> In a poll by ''[[The Daily Mirror]]'' in February 2010, Lohan was voted tenth on a list of "sexiest redheads ever".<ref name="redheads">{{cite news|url=http://www.mirror.co.uk/celebs/news/2010/02/05/girls-aloud-star-nicola-roberts-voted-sexiest-redhead-ever-115875-22021093/|title=Girls Aloud star Nicola Roberts voted sexiest redhead ever|last=Thompson|first=Jody|date=February 5, 2010|work=[[The Daily Mirror]]|publisher=[[Trinity Mirror]]|accessdate=19 April 2010}}</ref>

Lohan has a long-lasting obsession with [[Marilyn Monroe]] going back to when she saw ''[[Niagara (1953 film)|Niagara]]'' during the ''The Parent Trap'' shoot.<ref name="nymagmarilyn">{{cite web |url=http://nymag.com/fashion/08/spring/44247/ |title=Lindsay Lohan as Marilyn Monroe in "The Last Sitting" |quote=Photographs by [[Bert Stern]] |first=Amanda |last=Fortini |date=February 18, 2008 |publisher=[[New York (magazine)|NYmag.com]]}}</ref> In the 2008 ''Spring Fashion'' edition of ''New York'' magazine, Lohan re-created Monroe's final photo shoot, known as ''[[The Last Sitting]]'', including nudity, saying that the photo shoot was "an honor".<ref name="nymagmarilyn" /> The ''[[New York Times]]'' critic [[Ginia Bellafante]] found it disturbing, saying "the pictures ask viewers to engage in a kind of mock necrophilia.&nbsp;... At 21 [Lohan] seems even older than Monroe, who was 36 in the originals&nbsp;... [and] the photographs bear none of Monroe's fragility".<ref>{{cite news |last=Bellafante |first=Ginia |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/02/21/arts/21loha.htm |title=Lohan Assumes the Pose: Monroe<U+2019>s Final Sitting |work=[[The New York Times]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |date=February 21, 2008 |accessdate=October 25, 2009 }}</ref>

In 2008, Lohan launched a clothes line, whose name ''[[6126 Collection|6126]]'' was designed to represent Monroe's birth date (June 1, 1926). The line started with [[leggings]], before expanding to a full collection, covering 280 pieces as of April 2010.<ref name="leggings">{{cite news|url=http://www.metro.co.uk/metrolife/820783-lindsay-lohans-sexy-photoshoot-for-her-own-6126-fashion-line|title=Lindsay Lohan's sexy photoshoot for her own 6126 fashion line |date=April 8, 2010|work=[[Metro (Associated Metro Limited)|Metro]]|publisher=[[Associated Newspapers Limited]]|accessdate=April 20, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2010/apr/18/image/la-ig-diary18-20100418|title=Lindsay Lohan<U+2019>s 6126 stretches beyond leggings|last=Moore|first=Booth|date=April 18, 2010|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|publisher=[[Tribune Company]]|accessdate=20 April 2010}}</ref> In April 2009, Lohan released a [[Sunless tanning|self-tanning]] spray under the brand name ''Sevin Nyne'' in collaboration with [[Sephora]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.etonline.com/news/2008/07/63388/index.html |title=Lindsay Lohan's Leggings Now on Sale |date=July 15, 2008 |work=ET online |publisher=[[CBS]] |accessdate=April 19, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eonline.com/uberblog/b121671_lindsay_very_happy_in_touch_with.html |title=Lindsay "Very Happy," "in Touch" With Samantha |date=May 1, 2009 |work=[[E!]] |accessdate=April 19, 2010 |quote=the launch of her Sevin Nyne spray-tanning line in Santa Monica last night. }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/health/5256949/Lindsay-Lohans-new-fake-tan-sunshine-in-a-bottle.html |title=Lindsay Lohan's new fake tan: sunshine in a bottle |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |accessdate=April 19, 2010 |date=May 5, 2009 | location=London | first=Melissa | last=Whitworth}}</ref> In September 2009, Lohan became an artistic adviser for the French fashion house [[Emanuel Ungaro]];<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2009/sep/09/lindsay-lohan-joins-ungaro-artistic-adviser/ |title=Lindsay Lohan joins Ungaro as artistic adviser |agency=Associated Press |date=September 9, 2009 |accessdate=October 28, 2009 }}</ref> a collection by designer [[Estrella Archs]] with Lohan as adviser was presented in October, receiving a "disastrous" reception, according to ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' and ''[[New York (magazine)|New York]]''.<ref name="ewungaro">{{cite web |url=http://popwatch.ew.com/2009/10/05/lindsay-lohans-disastrous-paris-debut/ |title=Quelle horreur! Lindsay Lohan's disastrous Paris debut |date=October 5, 2009 |first=Missy |last=Schwartz |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |accessdate=October 28, 2009 }}</ref><ref name="nyungaro">{{cite web |url=http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2009/10/lindsay_lohans_ungaro_debut_de.html |title=Lindsay Lohan<U+2019>s Ungaro Debut Deemed Disastrous |date=October 5, 2009 |first=Amy |last=Odell |work=[[New York Magazine]] |accessdate=October 28, 2009 }}</ref> Lohan left the company in March 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2010/03/lindsay_lohan_out_at_ungaro.html |title=Lindsay Lohan Out at Ungaro |date=March 9, 2010 |first=Amy |last=Odell |work=[[New York Magazine]] |accessdate=March 12, 2009 }}</ref>

Having undergone rehabilitation for drug and alcohol addiction, Lohan, who has suffered from [[asthma]] since the age of two, is a [[Tobacco smoking|smoker]].<ref>{{harvnb|Peretz|2006|p=}}. {{" '}}Lindsay has had bronchial asthma since she was two,' Dina says"</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Apodaca|2008|p=}}. "One thing Lindsay can't give up (right now) is smoking, an addiction that she, like many others who've undergone alcohol and drug rehab, retains despite her asthma and despite the nagging throat clearing today that interrupts the conversation."</ref>

In the aftermath of the [[2010 Haiti earthquake|Haiti earthquake]] in March 2010, Lohan gave fund-raising assistance to the [[British Red Cross]] to provide aid for the country.<ref name="red cross">{{cite web|url=http://www.redcross.org.uk/news.asp?id=103649 |title=Lindsay Lohan auctions day out with her in LA to raise money for Haiti |last=Holloway |first=Heron |date=March 12, 2010 |publisher=[[British Red Cross]] |accessdate=March 13, 2010}}</ref> That same month, Lohan commenced legal proceedings in which she sought $100&nbsp;million from financial services company [[E*Trade]] for a television advertisement that Lohan claimed invoked her likeness without her permission.<ref name="E*Trade">{{cite news|url=http://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/industry-news/marketing/why-lindsay-lohan-is-not-the-etrade-baby/article1497805/|title=Why Lindsay Lohan is not the E*Trade baby|work=[[Globe and Mail]]|publisher=[[CTVglobemedia]]|accessdate=March 13, 2010}}</ref> She appeared on British comedy [[chat show]] ''[[Alan Carr: Chatty Man]]'' on March 11, 2010, during which she spoke about her fashion work and her fascination with Marilyn Monroe, and refused to answer questions from host [[Alan Carr]] about her sexuality.<ref name="DS Carr int">{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/showbiz/news/a207653/lohan-stays-tight-lipped-on-sexuality.html|title=Lohan stays tight-lipped on sexuality|last=Nissim|first=Mayer|date=9 March 2010|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=Digital Spy Ltd|accessdate=13 March 2010}}</ref>

